cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.EM, cs.LO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the development of reversible logic, which can be considered an emerging technology in the field of digital design. 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper presents a novel architecture for a reversible ROM, which falls under the category of digital system architecture. 
- cs.DC (Digital Circuits): The paper proposes new reversible gates and circuits, which are implemented using CMOS-based pass transistor logic. This falls under the category of digital circuit design. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper discusses the power dissipation associated with irreversible logic, which can be related to electromagnetic effects in digital circuits. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper deals with the design and optimization of reversible logic circuits, which falls under the category of logic in computer science.
